Hi I have a MAUI app with a SKCanvasView decalared as this
<skia:SKCanvasView  WidthRequest="1300" HeightRequest="1300" x:Name="GpuView" PaintSurface="OnPaintCanvas"								
gnorePixelScaling="True"	
                   VerticalOptions="Start"
orizontalOptions="Start" />
i call OnPaintCanvas in codebehind and it works with 
                            Application.Current.Dispatcher.Dispatch(() =>
                            {
                                if (GpuView != null)
                                    GpuView.InvalidateSurface();
                            });

Now i tried this in Blazor
  <SkiaSharp.Views.Blazor.SKCanvasView     Width="1024px" Height="1024px"  id=@CanvasID  OnPaintSurface="OnPaintCanvas" EnableRenderLoop="false" />

How do I call OnPaintCanvas from codebehind in Blazor,  it is called if i declare EnableRenderLoop="true"  but I want to call it myself to save CPU and later on GPU when SKGLView works in Blazor 
Thanks
